<PluginConfig>
    <Field id="infoLabel0" type="label" fontSize='large' fontColor="black">
        <Field id="sep7c" type="separator"/>

        <Label>AppleTV Device Indigo Plugin</Label>
    </Field>
    <Field id="space0" type="label" fontColor="black">
        <Label>Developed by: GlennNZ</Label>
    </Field>
        <Field id="sepa37" type="separator"/>
   <Field id="infoLabel01" type="label" fontSize='large' fontColor="blue">
        <Label>Press the Below button to Generate Indigo Plugin AppleTV Devices.  They are created in main directory and thereafter can be moved.

If need arises, can re-press whenever new appleTV's added, and if any unneeded devices just delete.

If you cannot connect to your device, try power cycling it first, or allocate it a fixed IP address and use the Scan single IP address feature below.
        </Label>
    </Field>
        <Field id="sep7121ab" type="separator"/>
    <Field id="forceDiscovery" type="checkbox" defaultValue="false" tooltip="Enabling will discovery all devices including non-appleTVs .">
